Photo shows officials and health professionals visiting the Bashundhara COVID-19 Isolation Hospital (Temporary Health Centre) shortly after its inauguration in Dhaka, Bangladesh on May 17, 2020. As the COVID-19 pandemic continues unabated, the Bangladeshi government has begun ramping up makeshift quarantine and hospital facilities in the capital Dhaka and elsewhere in the country.Photo:Xinhua 

